http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Motorcycle-rider-mowed-down-by-bus/article14010078.ece

A 26-year-old motorcycle rider was killed on the spot when a BMTC bus knocked him down at BEL Circle on Wednesday. He has been identified as Ranganath, a private firm employee, who was on his way to office. Police said Ranganath was trying to jump the signal when the mishap occurred. The Jalahalli police have seized the bus and detained the driver for questioning.